# Async Code Style

Always use `async/await`. Never use `.then()`, `.catch()`, or `.finally()` chains.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
fetchUser(id)
  .then((user) => setUser(user))
  .catch((err) => console.error(err))

// ✅ GOOD
try {
  const user = await fetchUser(id)
  setUser(user)
} catch (err) {
  console.error(err)
}
```

- Wrap `await` calls in `try/catch` — never swallow errors silently.
- For concurrent independent calls use `Promise.all` with `await`, not chained `.then()`:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const [user, orders] = await Promise.all([fetchUser(id), fetchOrders(id)])
```
